info:
For these to work, you have to:

```bash
cd ~/.node-red
npm install TotallyInformation/node-drayton-wiser
```

Then change settings.js to include:

```javascript
// ...
functionGlobalContext: {
    // ...
    wiser: require('node-drayton-wiser')(),
    // ...
},
// ...
```

That gives you a single instance of the wiser
function that you can then simply reference 
in multiple function nodes by including

```javascript
const wiser = global.get('wiser')
```

at the start of each node.

